# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Docker build-context excludes for the build-from-source frontend image
# (docker/Dockerfile). The image runs `npm ci && npx gulp deploy` from local
# submodule source, so the manifests (package.json, package-lock.json), the
# build tooling (gulpfile.js, gulp-utils.js, tsconfig.json, .babelrc,
# locales.js) and ALL source (app/, app-loader/, elements.js, conf/, scripts/,
# emojis/, extras/, svg/…) MUST reach the build context.
#
# The stock ignore file was a whitelist (`*` + a few docker/ files) that
# excluded exactly those manifests/source, so no React bundle was ever built
# and the running stack served the stock prebuilt 6.10.3 dist (finding C10).
# This is the narrow relaxation: everything is INCLUDED except the heavy,
# regenerated, or VCS/CI/editor artifacts listed below — nothing else.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Installed/vendored deps — reinstalled deterministically by `npm ci` in-image.
node_modules

# Build output & caches — regenerated by `npx gulp deploy` inside the image.
dist
tmp
coverage
.sass-cache

# VCS / CI / localization-service / editor metadata — not needed to build.
.git
.github
.tx

# Test harnesses & committed parity evidence — not part of the served bundle
# (the production build entry is app/react/index.tsx; specs are never imported).
e2e
e2e-react

# Logs & OS cruft.
**/*.log
npm-debug.log*
.DS_Store
